member.summary: Returns a list of dependent responses. Example: "Laerdal.Response.Ecg.Severity" depends on the value of "Laerdal.Response.Ecg.BasicRhythm". This means that if BasicRhythm=HYPER_KALEMIA then numeric range of Severity is 1-4, on other cases 1-3. This varies depending on manikin. At the time of writing this these responses have dependent settings: Laerdal.Response.Ecg.Extrasystole, Laerdal.Response.Ecg.HeartRate_bpm, Laerdal.Response.Ecg.Severity, and they are all dependent on Laerdal.Response.Ecg.BasicRhythm. Returns the empty list if there are no dependencies.

member.summary: Returns the settings for a specific manikin. If this response requires a list of dependent responses, you must supply this also, otherwise an exception will be thrown. Use the 'DependsOn' property to check for the need of adding this dependent response values. Returns null if the manikin is not supported, i.e. the settings are unknown.
member.param: The manikin to check settings for. If null, the default settings are returned

member.param: The name or IP address of the server to connect to

A delegate which will be called if the connection to the server is lost. Specify null if no action should be taken when the connection is lost. This delegate could contain some information to the user and give the possibility to connect to the server again. This delegate will not be called immediately when the connection is lost but first when the client tries to communicate with the server, for example to retrieve a parameter value, but fails doing so. If immediate knowledge about a lost connection is needed the CheckConnection() function could be called for example each second. If the argument given to the delegate it true, then the simulation engine did shutdown and can't be reconnected to. This should cause your application to shutdown gracefully also, asking the user to check the simulator and reconnect when it is started again.
member.returns: Returns true if the connection to the server succeeded

member.name: M:LaerdalSimulatorAPI.IManikin.RemoveClient
member.summary: Removes the current client. Used as a preparation for Disconnect() when you want to connect again using the same process. See the unit tests for how to use. There need to be a 1500msec sleep after RemoveClient() before Disconnect(), in order for the server to process removal of the client instance.
